{{Quote|Hang on! I'm going to pull a drop-kick Koiogran turn!|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] to [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], while being [[Rescue on Myrkr|pursued]] by [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]]|<ref name="Heir to the Empire 4">[[Heir to the Empire 4|''Heir to the Empire'' 4]]</ref>}}
A '''Koiogran turn''', or '''drop-kick Koiogran turn''', was a [[Starfighter combat/Legends|combat]] maneuver developed by [[Kendra Novar]] that was utilized by [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] to escape pursuit. By pushing the throttle forward with one hand and twisting the control stick with the other, the [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] would lose all forward momentum and loop-roll in another direction.

==History==
While growing up on [[Pellezara station]], the young [[Tarrin Datch/Legends|Tarrin Datch]] would frequently be tasked with moving [[Freighter/Legends|freighters]] into designated parking slots while the [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] waited for their [[Starship/Legends|ships]] to be serviced. One time, Datch performed a miniature Koiogran turn in a [[Bulk freighter/Legends|bulk freighter]], destroying a dozen beacon pods in the process. He was grounded by his [[Tarrin Datch's father|father]], literally, for the stunt, being assigned to traffic control and resupply for three standard weeks.<ref name="GG3">[[Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back (Second Edition)|''Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back'', Second Edition]]</ref>

[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] unsuccessfully attempted to [[Rescue on Myrkr|escape]] from [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] by using a drop-kick Koiogran turn when they were both flying [[GAT-12 Skipray Blastboat|Skipray Blastboats]] in the atmosphere of [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]]. Luke, unfamiliar with the craft at the time, accidentally hit the top of the treeline after losing his forward momentum and caused both craft to plummet into the forest below.<ref name="Heir to the Empire">''[[Heir to the Empire]]''</ref>

During the [[skirmish at Chazwa]], the ''[[Kern's Pride]]'' used a sort of mutated drop-kick Koiogran maneuver to attempt to escape two [[Lancer-class frigate/Legends|''Lancer''-class frigates]]. The frigates, however, were not fooled a bit by the ploy and kept pursuing the modified [[CR90 corvette/Legends|CR90 corvette]].<ref name="The Last Command">''[[The Last Command]]''</ref>

Sometime during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the Koiogran turn was introduced into both Imperial and Alliance [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] corps as a possible way to not only escape pursuit, but create a situation in which a pilot can turn his weapons against a would-be attacker.<ref>''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Miniatures Game]]''</ref>

